Abdomen blackish brown, with venter slightly paler. Tenth tergum in lateral view subquadrate, roundly produced posteriorly (
Fig. 14
); in dorsal view apex distinctly inflated (
Fig. 16
). Tenth sternum (
Figs. 14–15
) strongly sclerotized, ventrally 2.5 times longer than wide, proximal margin V–shaped, distal margin slightly incised; in lateral view spoon–like, slightly curved dorsad, with apex strongly inflated.

Eighth sternum subtrapezoidal in lateral view, with distal margin strongly produced posteriorly. Tenth tergum (
Fig. 17
) short, triangular in lateral view. Gonocoxite (
Fig. 17
) membranous, subquadrate, obliquely directed dorsad.
